francis patrelle is a choreographer who uses 
classical and neoclassical ballet to create characters in dance he 
also has enough inventiveness to remain interesting and not keep 
repeating himself without getting way out 
dances patrelle formed a year ago is holding its first 
oneweek season at florence gould hall in the french institute 
most of the dancers are guests from established companies the idea 
of the company is to show patrelles choreography as effectively as 
possible 
on wednesday the second night the program began with adieu 
with a handshake with peter boal of the new york city ballet as 
vincent van gogh james jordan as his brother theo who tried 
unsuccessfully to sell his paintings and jana fugate as theos 
wife they danced to a debussy recording 
boals part became increasingly searching reaching extending 
anxious the other two responded sometimes affectionately 
sometimes coldly to his thrusts into their midst we like that 
ballet best 
two pleasing pas de deux followed judith fugate of the new york 
city ballet and medhi bahiri danced fantasy pas de deux from 
belovedmemories patrelle choreographed that for cynthia 
gregory and fernando bujones together performances at the city 
center last september 
patrelle who was born in bucks county pa was resident 
choreographer for the berkshire ballet from 1974 to 84 and created 
a fulllength romeo and juliet there jana fugate and jordan 
danced the balcony scene it was full of romance but didnt 
build instead of meeting shyly and falling more and more in love 
the dancers met with familiarity 
the final dance come raincome shine is 55 minutes long 
and was new in 1986 when it starred merrill ashley of the new york 
city ballet this season it stars cynthia gregory of american 
ballet theater she brings the strength of assurance to it when 
she and her partner donald williams of the dance theater of 
harlem are dancing one is enthralled 
the music is recordings by judy garland the concept however 
seems forced onto the songs the stage is a boxing ring hwere three 
couples do maritalbattle dances 
