sigourney weaver nominated for both lead and 
supporting actress awards became the first such dual nominee in 
oscar history not to win in either category 
she received a best actress nomination for her portrayal of 
famed primate researcher dian fossey in gorillas in the mist 
it was miss weavers second nomination in this category with her 
role in 1986s aliens the first 
miss weaver also was nominated for her supporting performance as 
the no holdsbarred wall street boss in working girl a 
character she described as a tycoonsharkess 
the four performers before her who were nominated in both 
leading and supporting categories include jessica lange who in 
1982 was nominated for the lead in frances and won for her 
supporting part in tootsie 
others were barry fitzgerald who in 1944 played the lead in 
going my way but won for the supporting role in the same film 
teresa wright nominated for the lead in 1942s the pride of the 
yankees and won for her supporting role in mrs miniver and 
fay bainter who was nominated for the lead in 1938s white 
banners and won for her supporting role in jezebel 
