<TEXT>
millions of americans with arthritis must 
decide between enduring painful swollen joints or risking the 
development of a bleeding gastric ulcer according to a new survey 
of physicians 
the arthritis foundation said that a survey of 1009 physicians 
who treat arthritis patients showed that 93 percent of the doctors 
believe that aspirin ibuprofen and some prescription 
antiinflammatory drugs are the most useful of a limited number of 
medications available to treat arthritis 
but the survey also found that 81 percent of the doctors regard 
ulcers and other digestive problems to be the most serious 
complication in the treatment of arthritis the survey was released 
today 
when you look at the number of patients who take this 
medication it becomes a major health problem said dr naurang 
m agrawal a physician on an arthritis foundation advisory panel 
he said about one in every five arthritis patients taking aspirin 
and the other socalled nonsteroidal antiinflammatory drugs 
nsaids develop some type of gastric problem as a result 
and yet he said the nsaids remain the most effective drugs for 
control of the pain and swelling from arthritis 
the arthritis foundation said in a statement that in the united 
states about 37 million men women and children about one in 
every seven americans suffer from some form of arthritis 
arthritis is actually a family of more than 100 specific diseases 
but the most common are osteroarthritis and rheumatoid arthritis 
there is no cure for either of these common forms and treatment 
for both concentrates on relieving joint pain swelling stiffness 
and other symptoms 
osteroarthritis the most common form affects the elderly the 
most often and few who live past 60 escape at least a mild symptom 
in severe cases joints degenerate until they are useless and in 
some cases must be surgically replaced by implants 
rheumatoid arthritis strikes usually in middle age and can lead 
quickly to disability in severe cases in addition to joint 
swelling and pain symptoms can include fever and fatigue 
both of these types of arthritis are characterized by 
inflammation in the joints aspirin and other nsaids are effective 
because they control inflammation by inhibiting the production of 
prostaglandin a hormonelike protein that is active in the 
inflammation process 
but agrawal said that while the nsaids block prostaglandins at 
the joints the drugs also deplete the hormones in the stomach and 
intestines where prostaglandins provide protection from ulcer 
development 
the result said agrawal is that arthritis patients are 
relieved of joint pain but then may suddenly develop ulcers 
it is a very serious problem that is just now being addressed 
seriously he said 
the danger of developing ulcers applies mostly to those who must 
take large daily doses of the nsaids in order to control 
inflammation occasional aspirins or other headache medicines post 
little ulcer hazard experts say 
last december the food and drug administration recognized the 
problem by ordering that nsaids carry warnings about ulcers or 
damage to the stomach from a chronic daily dosage 
the fda recently approved a new drug misoprostol for the 
prevention of gastric ulcers caused by chronic nsaid medication 
the drug marketed as cytotec by g d searle amp co permits most 
arthritis patients to take antiinflammatory drugs without risking 
ulcers but misoprostol can promote diarrhea in some patients and 
can cause miscarriage in pregnant women 
</TEXT>
