six black activists left the 
british embassy today a day after encamping there to protest 
police restrictions on their activities an escaped detaineee 
remained in the us consulate 
almost as soon as the six activists arrived at the british 
embassy in pretoria on wednesday british officials made clear they 
disapproved of the protest and asked that the group leave 
the activists left today after having requested britain to 
pressure the south african government to lift all restrictions on 
them and other former detainees foreign minister rf botha said 
the five men and one woman would not be arrested 
