to protest their detention without trial 
the government announced wednesday that it would now place 
hunger strikers in prison or in hospitals in bloemfontein a 
relatively remote provincial center to prevent escapes and 
publicity about them 
authorities have freed most detainees since the fasts began but 
has placed severe restrictions on their activities human rights 
sources say several hundred remain in detention including more 
than 30 on hunger strikes 
an estimated 30000 people have been detained for varying 
periods under the emergency declared in june 1986 
under apartheid the countrys 28 million blacks have no vote in 
national affairs the 5 million whites control the economy and 
maintain separate districts schools and health services 
