<TEXT>
the federal government today said it wont 
take over cleanup of the nations worstever oil spill but will 
watch closely because of the slicks enormous potential for 
damage to the environment 
the 500squaremile slick continued to spread uncontained by 
the efforts of 444 personnel from the coast guard and other 
agencies and dozens of fishermen backed by three coast guard 
helicopters two cutters 33 contract vessels five tugboats and a 
dozen skimmers 
only 6000 barrels of the 240000 that spilled from an exxon 
tanker friday have been recovered officials said 
anyone who goes up and looks at the slick has to be humbled by 
it said chief petty officer todd nelson 
at the white house transportation secretary samuel skinner 
environmental protection agency administrator william reilly and 
coast guard commandant adm paul yost reported their firsthand 
observations to president bush who decided against a federal 
takeover 
bush gave top priority to assessing the adequacy of 
environmental protection reilly said 
this is obviously a disaster of enormous potential magnitude 
on the environment reilly said the habitats of sea otters and 
