administration inherited from our predecessors but i dont have 
anything this morning that i can give you by way of new policy or a 
new idea 
asked if he had any reason to think that elections in panama 
could be conducted democratically he replied theres always 
hope chicagos been reformed why not panama 
cheney also said that philosophically he had no problem with 
applying the death penalty in serious cases of peacetime espionage 
several arrests have been made in recent months in spy cases that 
have been described as potentially serious enough to justify a 
prosecution request for capital punishment 
cheney also said he couldnt support any type of compulsory 
national service plan for americans when they turn 18 but 
wouldnt object to a carefully crafted voluntary plan that 
recognized the need to staff the allvolunteer military 
in addition he said he and rep les aspin dwis would simply 
have to disagree about the role of top military officers in dealing 
with congress 
aspin chairman of the house armed services committee 
criticized cheney on wednesday for scolding the air forces top 
general for consulting privately with congressional leaders on 
missile programs aspin argued that contacts between congress and 
the military are not adequate as it is 
cheney responded thursday he considered aspin a close friend 
but hadnt changed his mind about having civilian executives handle 
such consultations 
cheney also said he had received several greetings from foreign 
defense ministers including the one from the soviet union since 
taking office cheney said he thought it would be useful to meet 
the soviet defense chief but that nothing was scheduled 
the baseclosing initiative began last year with an independent 
commission crafting a plan to close 86 installations most of them 
relatively small and to partially close five others for a 
projected savings of 56 billion over 20 years 
despite some opposition those closures appear likely opponents 
do not appear to have the votes needed in congress to block the 
plan 
