continue as gannett executive vice president for news until his 
retirement in october 1990 curley said 
neuharth 65 announced march 22 that he is also resigning from 
the companys board of directors effective at the annual 
shareholders meeting in chicago april 27 he will continue to 
write his weekly column for usa today 
curley 50 will be gannetts fourth chairman and chief 
executive officer he has been president of gannett since 1984 and 
chief executive officer since 1986 he joined gannett in 1969 as an 
editor at the timesunion in rochester ny he held editor and 
publisher posts at gannett newspapers in new jersey and delaware 
and served as general manager of the gannett news service 
neuharth has been a gannett executive for 26 years he was named 
president and chief operating officer in 1970 president and chief 
executive officer in 1973 and president chief executive officer 
and chairman in 1979 he is the founder of usa today 
quinn 63 had been editor of the national newspaper for five 
years before becoming editor in chief in 1988 
the announcement said quinns responsibilities will be assumed 
by peter s prichard editor since 1988 and ronald d martin 
executive editor since the newspaper began publication in 1982 
they will continue to have their present titles 
gannett publishes 85 daily newspapers 35 nondaily newspapers 
and usa weekend a newspaper magazine it operates 10 television 
stations 16 radio stations gannett news services and an outdoor 
advertising company 
