confessed to charges of transferring secret information to the 
enemy and having contacts with enemy agents he told the court he 
asked for 15 million in return for the information the radio 
reported 
shenkman who reportedly became disillusioned with israeli 
society after immigrating here from the soviet union in 1978 never 
received any of the money he requested 
sentencing was set for april 12 the maximum term is 33 years 
shenkman told the court he visited athens greece three times 
in 1988 and gave plo officials information about his military 
service including the location of bases and names of commanders 
he also offered to fly to plo headquarters in tunis tunisia 
and hold a news conference where he would rip up his passport and 
say israel is a racist state the court heard 
shenkman served in the army for four months in 1985 it would be 
unusual for a new immigrant who served for a short time to hold a 
sensitive position 
shenkman was arrested at tel avivs bengurion airport upon his 
return from his third visit to athens 
his was the second recent case of espionage involving a soviet 
