<TEXT>
problemplagued turkey points only working nuclear 
reactor remained shut down thursday until florida power amp light co 
can prove to federal inspectors its staff knows how to operate the 
plant safely 
the utility took the unit off line wednesday when the nuclear 
regulatory commission announced that half of the key control room 
operators tested had failed their routine yearly requalification 
exam that immediately barred them from running the plant 
eleven of 24 operators and three of six teams who are tested 
on their ability to work together failed all or part of the exam 
said nrc spokesman ken clark 
the results were so worrisome the nrc is sending a special team 
to review the performance of all control room staff at the plant 
located on the atlantic coast about 20 miles south of miami 
we want to take a look at the rest of the operators too even 
the ones who have passed the nrc exam clark said thursday we 
have questions now about the adequacy of their training program 
those who failed must be retrained and recertified by the nrc 
before they are allowed back into the control room the florida 
utility says it hopes to complete all the testing within a week 
if we are satisfed the plant will probably be allowed to go 
back on line clark said 
the utility must also file a full report with the nrc by may 1 
detailing how the company will upgrade training to satisfactory 
levels 
utility spokeswoman stacey shaw minimized the training 
difficulties on thursday calling the failure rate an unusual 
circumstance 
more than half of those who failed the exam were inactive 
management personnel who no longer work in the control room but 
maintain their licenses she said in all the utility has 52 
licensed operators of which 40 actually work in the control rooms 
she insisted the utility voluntarily shut down unit 3 on 
wednesday although clark said the nrc would not have accepted 
anything less 
antinuclear activist joette lorion who has conducted a 
onewoman crusade against turkey point for years said the test 
failures are extremely serious 
operators of nuclear plants are very important she said 
weve seen in accidents such as three mile island and chernobyl 
that operator error greatly contributed to and in some cases even 
caused the accidents 
the nrc has hit turkey point with about 1 million in fines over 
the past five years for safety and security violations identifying 
the plant as one of the nations ten worst ralph naders public 
citizen environmental group has also called it one of the 
worstmanaged commercial facilities 
last year the florida utility was forced by the nrc to overhaul 
turkey points management after a series of incidents including a 
leak that severely corroded a giant bolt holding the reactor vessel 
together guards found asleep on duty unescorted visitors in 
sensitive areas leaks from the spent fuel pool and other problems 
