<TEXT>
a frenchmans exhausting effort to beat a 
monthold new yorktosan francisco sailing speed record fell just 
a few agonizing hours short on thursday after an 81day 
14500mile journey 
a tired and bloody philippe monnet steered his battered trimaran 
under the golden gate three days after he threw his food overboard 
to lighten his boats load and squeeze out another knot or two he 
had gone four days without sleep 
monnet 29 lost his bid for the record after a series of 
heartbreaking setbacks including a brush with a submerged iceberg 
off cape horn that cost him a week for repairs and a tussle with 
18foot seas and capricious winds off the california coast 
but monnet became the first sailor to make the voyage alone and 
appeared jubilant as he bounded out of the cabin of the 60foot 
elle et vire arms raised to greet a crowd of wellwishers at pier 
39 
leaping onto the deck as the boat was tied up he received a 
kiss from his girlfriend and popped the cork of a bottle of french 
champagne 
later on the dock he said simply i am very tired but i am 
here in san francisco my boat is here and it is good no 
asked if he would like to get away from his boat the 
indefatigable sailor looked puzzled shrugged and said i like 
sailing 
monnet needed to arrive at the golden gate by 734 am to snap 
the mark set feb 12 by the american sloop thursdays child which 
took 80 days and 20 hours port to port to break a 135yearold 
record 
in addition to his collision with an iceberg monnet slashed his 
hands and arms on monday after the main wire supporting his mast 
snapped off the coast of southern california monnet had to climb 
the mast and spent hours cutting the tangled sail away and 
repairing the vital cable 
michael fortenbaugh representing the manhatten yacht club 
which put up the clipper challenge cup trophy for the record 
attempt said that missing the record doesnt diminish monnets 
acheivement 
its sad and all that he missed the record but he is the 
first person to do it singlehanded fortenbaugh said his 
acheivement is not dimmed one bit 
plans call for monnet to catch the first available plane to new 
york and then to paris fortenbaugh said the ship will remain 
behind on view at touristy pier 39 
i dont know what the french will do with it after that he 
said 
somewhere to the south is another trimaran that had been trying 
for the record the 50foot finistere bretagne skippered by anne 
liardet 
with fiance joseph le guen as crew she started jan 1 from new 
york but was overtaken by monnet liardet was the first woman to 
attempt the new yorksan francisco challenge 
thursdays child crewed by skipper warren luhrs 44 alachua 
fla courtney hazleton 32 palmetto fla and lars bergstrom 
54 sarasota fla broke a record set by the clipper ship flying 
cloud in 1854 
