wideranging sports page carrying the latest in american 
basketball european soccer or asian table tennis 
our philosophy is to provide our readers with what is 
happening in china and what is happening in the world said 
deputy chief editor chen hui 
chinese press authorities began mulling the idea of an 
englishlanguage daily in 1979 the year china embarked on its 
economic reforms and opendoor policy before that nonchinese 
speakers or readers lived in a news vacuum except for several dull 
propagandafilled englishlanguage periodicals 
the china daily with technical assistance from the australian 
thomson foundation and the melbourne age began publishing june 1 
1981 with a first edition of 10000 copies 
within two years it had an airmailed north american edition and 
in 1987 began satellite transmissions to london for distribution in 
western europe besides london it now publishes in new york san 
francisco hong kong canton and shanghai 
originally printed five days a week the paper now comes out six 
days and has a fourpage business paper on sunday chen said 
domestic circulation has risen to about 130000 with twothirds of 
the readership being chinese 
chen said the daily which delivers to major hotels for 
foreigners is chinas first not to depend entirely on the plodding 
post office for distribution it is also the first with about 25 
percent of space devoted to ads to obtain a large percent of its 
revenues from advertisements 
the paper also is financed by sales it costs only 30 fen 8 
cents a copy and like all chinese papers government subsidies 
chen insists though that government backing does not make the 
china daily official papers like the communist partys 
peoples daily renmin ribao have the role of explaining 
government and party policies to the people thats not our 
purpose we cant get the foreigner to do anything 
the editorial board which puts together a weekly commentary and 
oversees daily articles is not subject to outside influence chen 
said 
but like all chinese media the china daily exercises 
selfcensorship and doesnt report for the sensationalism 
involved to widen readership chen said 
asked why the paper carries reports of strikes in poland but 
