complicated plan that allowed the parent company interco inc to 
fend off a 27 billion hostile takeover 
the fourmonth fight by interco is the kind of saga thats 
become more common in the mergermania 80s a fortune 500 company 
facing two thirtysomething corporate raiders and duking it out in a 
fight that leaves many outside the ring bloodied and dazed 
its also a story of how a hostile takeover bid can be a 
moneymaker for those with the least stake in the company 
financiers and lawyers and a heartbreaker for those with the most 
basic vested interest the loyal employees 
