the center is asking state attorneys general to determine 
whether the undisclosed placement of commercial products in films 
constitutes deceptive advertising that violates state laws 
it also said broadcasting movies on television in which there 
are paid placements of cigarettes violates a 1971 law that 
prohibits advertising of cigarettes on tv 
mitchell said the center urged states to require filmmakers to 
state at the beginning of a movie for example notice this film 
contains paid advertising for marlboro cigarettes 
the center also said it would ask state officials to determine 
whether the placement of alcoholic beverages and cigarettes in 
youthoriented films should be prohibited because youths cannot 
legally buy such products 
